Package: aesInput
Type: Package
Title: Choose Colors, Shapes, or Patterns for each Selectize Option in Shiny.
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Daniel P.", "Smith", 
    email = "dansmith@orst.edu", 
    role  = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2479-2044"))
Description:
    Extends the Selectize dropdown box in Shiny to provide popovers
    within each selected value to select a color, shape, or pattern to
    associate with that value. This enables creating plots with
    user-specified aesthetics without needing additional contols.
URL: https://cmmr.github.io/aesInput/index.html
BugReports: https://github.com/cmmr/aesInput/issues
License: AGPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Additional_repositories: https://cmmr.github.io/aesInput
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    glue,
    magrittr,
    ggpattern,
    rlang,
    shiny
Suggests:
    ggpattern,
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
